located in src/scripts/reports.py, specifically in the arg parser arguments you can find all reports that could be made. Follow the next steps to produce the doc:
    1. Find all data dependencies referenced in data model and used in every report
    2. Write in a json file with the data dependencies to the report. In each node show the filename and the path to the data model (i.e data/pub/2026/roads.csv)
    3. If you find folders with multiple years use the last one.
    4. The final HTML should use the json file to generate the pipeline visualization, and be this should be responsive with a good style and minimal reqs.
    5. Save the HTML and the json in a folder inside docs/pipeline.

